  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4. that we would receive—omitted in the oldest manuscripts. Translate therefore, \"Beseeching of us … the grace and fellowship of (that is, to grant them the favor of sharing in) the ministering unto the saints.\" The Macedonian contributions must have been from Philippi, because Philippi was the only church that contributed to Paul's support (Php 4:10, 15, 16).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
