  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Praying us with much entreaty,.... They not only gave freely, being unasked by the apostles; but they sought to them, and earnestly entreated them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that they would receive the gift; the beneficence, what they had so freely and generously collected: and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the fellowship of the ministering to the saints; what they had communicated for the service of the poor saints at Jerusalem, in which they testified their having and holding fellowship with the churches of Christ; and that they would receive it at their hands, and take it upon them, and carry it to Jerusalem, and distribute to the poor saints there, as should seem to them most proper and convenient; which they accordingly agreed to; see Romans 15:25. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the fellowship of the ministering to the saints; what they had communicated for the service of the poor saints at Jerusalem, in which they testified their having and holding fellowship with the churches of Christ; and that they would receive it at their hands, and take it upon them, and carry it to Jerusalem, and distribute to the poor saints there, as should seem to them most proper and convenient; which they accordingly agreed to; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Romans 15:25",
